translationBlock.key: Creates a virtual inventory and holds it under the specified id. The string id should not be a UUID. If the id is already in use, an IllegalArgumentException will be thrown. You can use this id in other inventory functions to modify the contents, among other things. If a size is specified instead of a type, it is rounded up to the nearest multiple of 9. Size cannot be higher than 54. A title for the top of the inventory may be given, but it will use the default for that that inventory type if %s is specified. An optional inventory array may be specified, otherwise the inventory will start empty. Available inventory types: BREWING, CHEST, DISPENSER, DROPPER, ENDER_CHEST, FURNACE, HOPPER, PLAYER, WORKBENCH, ANVIL, SHULKER_BOX, BARREL, BLAST_FURNACE or SMOKER
